20/02/2004
OHRID, Macedonia -- The Second Balkan Youth Peace Conference opened in Ohrid on Thursday (19 February). The four-day event, organised by the Social Democrat Youth of Macedonia, will focus on youth unemployment, visa barriers faced by the young people of Southeast Europe, as well as their role in enhancing co-operation among countries in the region. The conference findings will be submitted to the Macedonian and Albanian parliaments. (Dnevnik - 20/02/04; MIA - 19/02/04)
